### Key Automation Commands

```
# Check workflow state (build rules, deploy status)
antimatter_execute command="workflow.state" projectId="{{PROJECT_ID}}"

# Check workflow errors
antimatter_execute command="workflow.errors" projectId="{{PROJECT_ID}}"

# Run a specific build rule manually
antimatter_execute command="workflow.run-rule/RULE_ID" projectId="{{PROJECT_ID}}"

# Emit a custom event to trigger rules
antimatter_execute command="workflow.emit" params={"event":{"type":"EVENT_TYPE"}} projectId="{{PROJECT_ID}}"
```

### Build Rules

Build automation is defined in `.antimatter/build.ts` on the workspace. Rules react to file changes and custom events, executing shell commands via `wf.exec()`. Check the current rules with `antimatter_execute command="workflow.state"`.

## Conventions

- The project ID must be passed to all `antimatter_*` tools as `projectId`
- All file paths are relative to the project root (e.g. `src/index.ts`, not absolute paths)
- Use `antimatter_files_tree` to explore the project structure before making changes
- Use `antimatter_execute command="workflow.state"` to check build/deploy status after changes
